# Tailwind CSS v4 Syntax

This project uses **Tailwind CSS v4**. Use the updated syntax:

## Dark Mode and Theme Variables (IMPORTANT)

Tailwind v4 uses CSS-first configuration. The correct setup in `globals.css`:

```css
@import "tailwindcss";

/* Enable class-based dark mode */
@custom-variant dark (&:where(.dark, .dark *));

/* Define theme variables with @theme directive */
@theme {
  --color-background: #ffffff;
  --color-foreground: #171717;
  /* ... other variables with --color- prefix */
}

/* Dark mode overrides (regular CSS, not @theme) */
.dark {
  --color-background: #0a0a0a;
  --color-foreground: #ededed;
}

/* Base styles */
html {
  color: var(--color-foreground);
  background: var(--color-background);
}
```

Key points:
- Use `@custom-variant dark` for class-based dark mode (NOT in tailwind.config.ts)
- Use `@theme { }` to register variables with Tailwind
- Use `--color-*` prefix for color variables (Tailwind v4 convention)
- Override in `.dark { }` selector for dark mode values
- The `darkMode: "class"` in tailwind.config.ts is for v3 compatibility only

## Gradients
- ❌ `bg-gradient-to-r` → ✅ `bg-linear-to-r`
- ❌ `bg-gradient-to-l` → ✅ `bg-linear-to-l`
- ❌ `bg-gradient-to-t` → ✅ `bg-linear-to-t`
- ❌ `bg-gradient-to-b` → ✅ `bg-linear-to-b`
- ❌ `bg-gradient-to-br` → ✅ `bg-linear-to-br`
- ❌ `bg-gradient-to-bl` → ✅ `bg-linear-to-bl`
- ❌ `bg-gradient-to-tr` → ✅ `bg-linear-to-tr`
- ❌ `bg-gradient-to-tl` → ✅ `bg-linear-to-tl`

The pre-commit hook will reject commits containing deprecated patterns.
